title: Ramen Noodle Crunch Salad
summary: Ramen Noodle Crunch Salad might be a good recipe to expand your main course recipe box. This recipe makes 4 servings with 859 calories, 15g of protein, and 61g of fat each. For $2.17 per serving, this recipe covers 39% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe from How Sweet Eats has 1 fans. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 1 hour. Head to the store and pick up ginger, carrot, sesame oil, and a few other things to make it today. It is a reasonably priced recipe for fans of Japanese food. It is a good option if you're following a dairy free diet. Overall, this recipe earns a very bad (but still fixable) spoonacular score of 0%. Try The BEST OG Ramen Noodle Salad, Ramen Noodle Salad, and Ramen Noodle Salad for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. You could try J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 22 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling
productMatches.description:
Despite its still youthful freshness it shows the fine fruity Riesling characteristic and an underlying hint of mineral from the blue/grey Devonian slate soil.

Serve this refreshing wine slightly chilled! As aperitif and, especially when more matured, in combination with seafood or poultry.

instructions:
Instructions

In a large bowl, combine the cabbage, kale, peppers, carrots, green onions, almonds and sunflower seeds. Break apart the ramen noodles and add them into the bowl. Toss everything together.

Whisk together the oils, vinegar, honey, lime juice, garlic, ginger and a pinch of salt and pepper. Pour the dressing over the cabbage mixture and toss well to coat. Toss continuously until everything is combined. Place the salad in the fridge for at least 30 minutes before serving.

Taste and season with more salt and pepper if needed. Serve cold!

You can make this ahead of time - even the night before! Just store it in the fridge. Toss well before serving.
